      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DOUBLE LOU (4) comes off a luckless fifth in the Chariots of Fire when held up on the pegs. Had won three of his other four attempts at this circuit and distance this time in including a Hondo Grattan victory from a wider barrier two back. Can bounce back. HESITATE (8) drew wide and raced three wide in the Chariots of Fire so did a good job to beat DOUBLE LOU home. Had kicked off his campaign with a G3 win from the back row at Melton prior. Big danger. NERANO NZ (10) draws deep but was good in his return to the Grimson yard, racing three wide without cover but sticking on for second. That was his first hitout for seven weeks so it should have improved him. There was plenty of merit in the latest performance of RIPP (6) when he drew wider and covered ground for third, 1.6m behind Nerano. Must respect. DARIN NZ (9) draws out so may need some luck but his form reads well.",
